        <updateDate>2019-09-20T18:38:02Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Stopping Threats On Pedestrians Act of 2019 or the STOP Act of 201</b><b>9</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Transportation (DOT) to establish a program to assist bollard installation projects designed to prevent pedestrian injuries and acts of terrorism in areas utilized by large numbers of pedestrians. Such a project is one that installs raised concrete or metal posts on a sidewalk adjacent to a roadway that are designed to slow or stop a motor vehicle.</p> <p>In carrying out the program, DOT may award competitive grants to local government entities.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
